{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it illegal to walk dogs during extreme heat to prevent suffering and death.",
        "additional_details": "Every year in the UK, dogs suffer and die from preventable heat-related illnesses. Many owners are unaware that dogs cannot regulate their body temperature effectively and can overheat within minutes.\r\n \r\nHot pavements can also cause severe burns to dogs\u2019 paws. When air temperatures reach 25\u00b0C, pavement temperatures can be significantly higher and dangerous.\r\n \r\nAnimal welfare organisations warn against walking dogs in hot weather.\r\n \r\nWe believe this legislation would help prevent unnecessary suffering, raise awareness, and hold owners accountable for avoidable harm.\r\n",
        "background": "Introduce legislation to make it an offence to walk or exercise dogs during dangerously high temperatures (i.e. 25\u00b0C and above), to protect them from heatstroke and burned paws.",
